# Current Goal

**Goal:** API Stabilization  
**Summary:** Origami is a graph-based agentic pipeline framework with Elements, Personas, Masks, Adversarial Dialectic, and a declarative YAML DSL. The framework is feature-complete. The goal is now API stabilization: freeze the public surface, harden documentation, and ensure the playground and README tell a coherent standalone story. Breaking changes require migration windows.

## Open Checklist

- [ ] Gate contracts complete — `signal-domains`, `signal-integrity`, `dialectic-hardening`
- [ ] Quick-win contracts complete — `resilience`, `ouroboros-signal-analysis`
- [ ] Public API surface is stable — no breaking changes pending (blocked by gate contracts)
- [ ] Test coverage on public interfaces is solid
- [ ] Root `README.md` positions Origami as a standalone framework (does not exist yet)
- [x] `examples/playground/` demonstrates all 9 concepts (Elements, Personas, DSL, Mermaid, Walk, Masks, Cycles, Dialectic, Team Walk)
- [x] `docs/framework-guide.md` covers Three CLIs, Extractors, Elements, Personas, DSL, Walk
- [x] `testdata/` contains canonical pipeline YAMLs: `defect-dialectic.yaml`, `defect-court.yaml`, `rca-investigation.yaml`; curation in `curate/testdata/`
- [x] `RichVocabulary` interface with `VocabEntry` wired into Kami, LSP, Kabuki
- [x] Thesis/Antithesis rename — terminology aligned with Hegelian dialectic model

## Execution Roadmap

```
Phase 1 — Gates (parallel where possible)
├── signal-domains        ← foundational, do first
├── dialectic-hardening   ← independent, parallel with signal-domains
└── signal-integrity      ← after signal-domains (uses zone domain labels)

Phase 2 — Quick-wins (parallel)
├── resilience
└── ouroboros-signal-analysis

Phase 3 — Finish line
├── Root README.md
├── Public API surface audit
└── Test coverage audit

Phase 4 — Vision (post-stabilization)
├── origami-lsp
└── washi
```

